Struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela&#8217;s daughter Zenani Mandela on Wednesday said Ahmed Kathrada was like a father to her.Mandela said this while paying tribute to struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada during a press briefing hosted by the Nelson Mandela Foundation. It is very important that I acknowledge that he was one of dad&#8217;s best friends. Let us honour what he and my father to stood for, said Mandela.She added Uncle Kathy was one of the last remaining men who fought for the liberation of our country .Khatrada (87) passed away on Tuesday morning at the Donald Gordon Hospital in Johannesburg after undergoing surgery to the brain.Meanwhile Executive Director of the Ahmed Kathrada Foundation Neeshan Balton said: This is great loss to the ANC, the broader liberation movement and South Africa as a whole. Internationally, he was staunch in his support for the Palestinian struggle. Kathy was an inspiration to millions in different parts of the world. Kathrada will be buried on Wednesday at 10am at the Westpark Cemetery, Beyers Naude Drive, Johannesburg.Meanwhile, CEO of the Nelson Mandela Foundation Sello Hatang said Today is not about being sad it&#8217;s a day about celebrating a life well lived. South Africa has lost one of its greatest, but we will continue to build the country of his dreams .-TNA Reporter 